[[File:Jawajawa_clan.jpg|thumb|The clan with their [[Unidentified Jawa Hero|hero]] in front.]]
This '''[[Jawa/Legends|Jawa]] clan''' managed to salvage a downed [[X-wing starfighter/Legends|X-wing]] [[Starfighter/Legends|starfighter]], and would later steal a [[TIE Advanced x1/Legends|TIE advanced]], believing it to be [[Anakin Skywalker/Legends|Darth Vader's]] personal fighter, from a trio of salvagers. Among the clan's members were the [[Unidentified Jawa Hero|TIE/Ad thief]], the [[Unidentified scarred Jawa|scarred warrior]], and a [[Unidentified Old Jawa|knowledgable aging Jawa]] who had insights into the [[Galactic Civil War/Legends|Galactic Civil War]].

==Behind the scenes==
This clan only appears in the story ''[[Oh!! Jawajawa]]'', published in ''[[Star Wars Manga: Silver]]'' issue of [[Tokyopop's Star Wars Manga]]. Originally published in Japan, those stories were considered to be of "fuzzy" continuity by Lucasfilm.<ref>{{SWBoards|url=thread.jspa?threadID=152583&start=980#15895005|thread=Holocron continuity database questions|user=[[Leland Chee|Leland Y Chee]]|date=2006-11-06|time=6:03 PM}}</ref> Since then, they have been republished in English in the United Kingdom under [[Infinities]] label, which established the material in them as [[Canon|non-canonical]].

